## Usage Rules

```cs
MA0165: Make interpolated string
MA0166: Forward the TimeProvider to methods that take one
MA0167: Use an overload with a TimeProvider argument
MA0171: Use pattern matching instead of inequality operators for discrete value
```

## MA0089: Optimize String Method Usage

```cs
dotnet_diagnostic.MA0089.severity = suggestion
```

## Optimize Enumerable.Count() Usage (MA0031)

```cs
dotnet_diagnostic.MA0031.severity = suggestion
```

## MA0089: Optimize string method usage

```cs
public class StringOptimizer {
    public void ProcessString(string input) {
        // Potentially inefficient:
        // if (input.ToLower().Contains("test")) { ... }

        // More efficient:
        if (input.Contains("test", StringComparison.OrdinalIgnoreCase)) { 
            // ...
        }

        // Consider using string.IsNullOrEmpty or string.IsNullOrWhiteSpace
        if (!string.IsNullOrEmpty(input)) {
            // ...
        }
    }
}
```

## Optimize String Method Usage in C#

```c#
string str;
str.StartsWith("a"); // non-compliant
str.StartsWith('a'); // ok

str.EndsWith("a"); // non-compliant
str.EndsWith('a'); // ok

str.Replace("a", "b"); // non-compliant
str.Replace('a', 'b'); // ok

str.IndexOf("a", StringComparison.Ordinal); // non-compliant
str.IndexOf('a'); // ok
```

## MA0089: Optimize string method usage

```C#
/*
Rule ID: MA0089
Category: Performance
Severity: Information
Description: Optimize string method usage.
*/

// Incorrect usage:
if (myString != null && myString != "") { }

// Correct usage:
if (!string.IsNullOrEmpty(myString)) { }
```

## Incorrect GetType() Usage on System.Type

```csharp
System.Type type = typeof(string);
type.GetType(); // non-compliant
```

## Variable Usage in Methods

```cs
// MA0153: Supports variables in methods.
public void MyMethod()
{
    var myVariable = 10;
    Console.WriteLine(myVariable);
}
```

## CancellationToken Overload Usage

```csharp
class Test
{
    public void A(CancellationToken cancellationToken)
    {
        MethodWithCancellationToken(); // non compliant
        MethodWithCancellationToken(cancellationToken); // compliant
    }

    public void MethodWithCancellationToken() => throw null;
    public void MethodWithCancellationToken(System.Threading.CancellationToken cancellationToken) => throw null;
}
```

## Attribute Usage Example

```csharp
// non-compliant
class SampleAttribute : System.Attribute { }

// ok
[System.AttributeUsage(System.AttributeTargets.Parameter)]
class SampleAttribute : System.Attribute { }
```
